# CVE-2026-33186: gRPC-Go auth bypass via missing leading slash in :path
# Transitive dependency pulled by Caddy (google.golang.org/grpc v1.79.1).
# Not exploitable: gRPC is only used by Caddy's localhost admin API, which
# is not exposed externally. Will be removed once Caddy bumps to grpc >= 1.79.3.
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2026-34986: go-jose/v3 DoS via crafted JWE (large p2c iteration count).
# Transitive dependency pulled by Caddy's ACME client (go-acme/lego).
# Not exploitable: we do not accept JWE-encoded input from external sources;
# this code path is exercised only against the ACME directory's CA, whose
# JWE responses we trust. Remove once Caddy bumps lego to a release that
# pulls go-jose/v3 >= 3.0.5.
CVE-2026-34986
